---
title: Slow Cooker Beef & Black Bean Chili Bar 2x the delicious servings!
description: Just like the lightbulb or zip-close bag, the slow cooker is one invention we can’t live without. There’s no lack of flavor when harmonious ingredients sit together cooking happily for hours without fuss. Case in point? This crowd-pleasing beef and black bean chili, packed with scallions, garlic, tomatoes, and all the quintessential spices. Serve this big batch meal to your hungry crowd with toppings galore, like scallion greens, tortilla chips, smoky red pepper crema, and cheddar cheese.

This recipe is double the typical servings, providing 4 servings and 8 servings for a 2 person and 4 person box respectively.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/64bfd0da8e7c223eb5b3647c-13e853e7.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/64bfd0da8e7c223eb5b3647c.pdf
author: HelloFresh
time required: 4 hours 15 minutes
cuisine: Southwest
nutrition:
  calories: 840 kcal
  fat: 44 g
  saturated fat: 17 g
  carbohydrates: 65 g
  sugar: 12 g
  protein: 42 g
  fiber: 12 g
  sodium: 1530 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/slow-cooker-beef-and-black-bean-chili-bar-64bfd0da8e7c223eb5b3647c
servings: 2
course: main course
---

Wash and dry produce.

Halve, core, and dice @long green pepper{1} into ½-inch pieces.

Peel and mince or grate @garlic{1%clove}.

Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens.

Place scallion greens in a #small bowl{} and cover with #plastic wrap{};
refrigerate until ready to serve.

Set a 5- to 6-quart #slow cooker{} to the sauté/brown setting and add a large
drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp}. Once oil is hot, add @ground beef{20%ounce},
green pepper, garlic, scallion whites, @Southwest spice blend{1%tbsp},
@Mexican spice blend{1%tbsp}, and a big pinch of @salt{pinch} and
@pepper{pinch}.

Cook, breaking meat up into pieces, until browned and mostly cooked through,
~{3-5%minutes}.

Stir in @tomato paste{1} and cook, stirring, until slightly darkened,
~{1-2%minutes}.

> TIP: No sauté setting on your slow cooker? No problem! Follow the same
> instructions using a large pan over medium-high heat, then transfer
> contents to slow cooker at the end of this step.

If there's excess grease in your slow cooker, carefully pour or spoon it out.

Stir in @beef stock concentrate{5}, @black beans{2} and their liquid, and
@diced tomatoes{14%ounce}. Cover and increase heat to high; cook until
tomatoes break down and flavors meld, ~{4-6%hours}.

Taste and season with salt and pepper.

When chili is ready to serve, dice @tomato{1} into ½-inch pieces.

Lightly crush @blue corn tortilla chips{1.5%ounce} in #bag{}.

Serve chili, scallion greens, tomato, tortilla chips, @smoky red pepper crema{4%tbsp}, and @cheddar cheese{1/2%cup} family style and let everyone build their own chili bowl!

> Ground beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.